<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100408870211108></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100408870211108><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100408870211108>RE: do pets lvl up</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100408870211108#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 26th 5:31 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Short answer:<br>****Nope****<br><br>Long answer:<br>****Nope****<br>But...<br><br>The level of your pet is random within a band.<br>The band values are set by the level of the spell you cast to summon the pet.<br><br>The L1 spell, summons a pet that is either always L1, or is L1, or L2.  (I can't remember which.)<br>The L2 spell summons a pet between L3 & L5.<br><br>As you get better and better pets, you will notice that the pet's level falls quite a way below yours.  (At L40 only the very best pet will con blue to you.)<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
