<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100402748190953></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100402748190953><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100402748190953>RE: Solo at 12?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100402748190953#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>108 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 25th 12:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another option in the same general area is the derv camp in NRO.  I'm talking about the one in the north section of the zone very close to the ocean where the dark elf spawns.  The dark elf will not aggro when you pull dervs and is not KOS to my Erudite necro.  There are three spawns here, two in the camp and one slightly to the east of the camp (towards the ocean).  You can pull the 'ocean' derv solo by parking pet next to the water and darknessing the derv.  Once you get him killed, head to the top of the hill just north of the camp.  This is tricky and sort of risky.  But, if you can break this camp you should be able to hold it fairly well.  To break the two spawns I fear the closer one and load the DoTs on the second one.  You will be lom, so sit and med until you get the message that your fear has worn off.  Then, get up and darkness the second derv.  The first one should be almost dead by now so you can kite the second around while pet finishes the first one off.  Then, you should hopefully have enough mana left to DoT, lifespike, or whatever the second derv to death.  <br><br>The xp here I would imagine is comparable to the green, scaly things in Oasis, and the loot will be much better.  The downside is that the risk will be a bit higher when breaking the two spawn this far away from the zone.  So, take it or leave it.  I'm having fun there at 13 and haven't died in a while.<br><br>-Yirruzen<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
