	   <tr><td colspan=2>Maybe you're smarter than you think...<br><br>You see, charisma has no bearing on necromancer fear spells or screaming terror.  This is why charisma is not a primary statistic for necromancers and shadow knights.  Don't be fooled by other people's rambling, flawed reasoning.<br><br>How do I know?  I'm a genius. Actually, that's my opinion based on playing a necro for a long while.  Hey, I could be wrong.  Think of it like this.  You're in oooh, say Frontier Mtns fighting giants.  Make them craigs for the sake of argument.  You're soloing one after another using fear/dot kiting.  Every so often you'll get one that resists darkness, or your DoT, or even FEAR consistantly (like 3+ times in a row).  Why? Because it's a simple resistance roll.  The duration is all luck too.  Why does it last 1 second sometimes, then you recast and it lasts 2 minutes?  Same reason.<br><br>Am I wrong? Hmmmm...<br><br>Astryl Abyssyl<br>50 Necromancer, Vazaelle <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
