	   <tr><td colspan=2>Without your best pet, your effectiveness will always be severely cut short...  I know this only too well, since I had this problem often...<br><br>There is no shame in buying the spell off another player...  And generally, this isn't too difficult.  What I would suggest, is that you start looking for spells a good way before you're going to need them.  I learned this the hard way.  If you wait until L24 to buy a spell for that level, you might well make another two levels, before you get it...  <br><br>Since this realisation sank in for me, I have started buying any and all spells I can...  (At L40, I have an L50 spell sitting in the bank...  It might be a while before I can scribe it, but I won't be moping around wishing I'd bought it earlier.)  <br><br>And of course, as with everything else, the best place to buy your words and spells tends to be East Commons.  (Is there anything that isn't for sale?  Because if there is, it's the only thing you can't auction for there!  *Grin*  (Please don't start bombarding me with, "You can't sell NO DROP items!"  I know.  :)  ))<br><br>Also, if you notice any necros in the L25-L30 region, they will be hunting the monsters you want words from.  Many necros ran small side-businesses, by making spells that have trivialled for them in research.  If you ask them, they might have made the spell you want...  (And who doesn't need just a few more plat, huh?)<br><br>As far as the cracked staff thing goes, I was constantly broke, until I hit L30.  You're almost outta the poverty zone kiddo.  Just stick with it.  <br><br>And very few people will ever down you for asking a question.  Don't sweat about that.  (Unless you're playing a naked elf and the question is, "Can I have your spare plat?"  Then you should sweat and hopefully feel ashamed and crawl under a rock.  Damned I hate those people.  *Growl*)<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br>"Death is coming..."<br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
