	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 22nd 3:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few comments about your post.<br><br>Level 53 necro pets are awesome for fear kiting.  They do have less HP than the level 49 pet, but if you are fear kiting, they do alot more damage.<br><br>Level 56 necro pets are good for damage output, but not as good as level 53 for fear kiting.  They will outdamage the level 49 pet...but have fewer hits...so not really tanks.  They will also outdamage a level 53 pet when not fear kiting or when there is no backstab opportunity.<br><br>Level 59 pets are the best tanks.  I expect their damage output will be better than the level 53 pet due to their lifetaps going off more often and having a higher damage.  I will find out more within a few weeks.<br><br>Necros can solo to 60 even with their level 49 pet...it will take you a while...but it can be done.  Jboots or SOW potions are required to safely solo from your early 40's on.<br><br>Kunark has some nice solo spots for necros. Late 40's until 56'ish can be done nicely in Burning Woods.  I find that zone underutilized...so not much contention for spawns...if you find the right spot.  51 plus can be done in SkyFire..it will just take you some time.  <br><br>Mid 30's into the late 40's can be done in Great Divide...you never have to leave that zone unless you want to...LOL!  Cept to go to the bank!  You can easily single pull the Tizmaks wandering between caves 2 and 3.  You can joing bear groups.  You can join Shardwurm groups.  You can do the Drakkel Wolves, Scouts, Berserkers...but stay away from the elites until you are well into your 50's.  The Frost Giant Elites will eat you up in GD.<br><br>You cannot beat the experience you can get in a good group.  Learn to group!  Or you will be a lonely necro..I highly recommend joining a good guild.<br><br>Ishtarra, Tunare Server, Defiler (58)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
